.TH "slim_stream_allocate" 9 "slim_stream_allocate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
slim_stream_allocate \- Allocate a new SLIMbus Stream
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct slim_stream_runtime *" slim_stream_allocate
.BI "(struct slim_device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Slim device to be associated with
.IP "name" 12
name of the stream
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is very first call for SLIMbus streaming, this API will allocate
a new SLIMbus stream and return a valid stream runtime pointer for client
to use it in subsequent stream apis. state of stream is set to ALLOCATED
.SH "RETURN"
valid pointer on success and error code on failure.
From ASoC DPCM framework, this state is linked to \fBstartup\fP operation.
